File: President Cyril Ramaphosa. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is meeting with political parties on Wednesday to discuss the country's response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Matters related to the national lockdown will also be discussed. READ: Schools to reopen on 1 June: Dept of Basic Education This virtual meeting is the third consultative meeting that the president is holding with political party leaders. This comes as the Democratic Alliance and the Freedom Front Plus both announced that they would be lodging legal challenges against some of the lockdown regulations. The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has increased to 17,200. The death toll has jumped to 312 and total recoveries are at 7,960. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.